This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new approach to recommender systems using stochastic multi-gradient descent. It also involves optimizing for multiple objectives, which is a common problem in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as recommender systems are often used in information retrieval applications. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as recommender systems are a common application of AI. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper involves optimizing for multiple objectives, which could involve the use of algorithms and data structures. 

Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as recommender systems are often used in social networks and involve analyzing user behavior and preferences.
